  "prompt": "Can you confirm if money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, **money laundering** is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other crimes) appear legitimate by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions.\n\n### Why Is It Illegal?\nMoney laundering undermines the integrity of financial systems, facilitates criminal activities, and can have severe economic and social consequences. It is often associated with organized crime, terrorism financing, and tax evasion.\n\n### Global Response\nGovernments and international organizations, such as the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**, have established strict laws and regulations to combat money laundering. Penalties for money laundering can include hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.\n\nIf you have any more specific questions or need further details, feel free to ask!",
